# Webhook Debugger - Project Structure

## Overview
This is a webhook debugger application built with Next.js 16, React 19, and TypeScript. The application allows users to receive, inspect, and debug webhook requests in real-time.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router)
- **UI Library**: React 19
- **Language**: TypeScript 5
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
- **Icons**: lucide-react
- **Data Storage**: Redis
- **Linting**: ESLint with Next.js config

## Project Structure
- [src/app/](mdc:src/app/) - Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout
- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - Home page
- [public/](mdc:public/) - Static assets

## Key Principles
1. All code must be written in English
2. All user-facing messages and responses in Portuguese
3. Use TypeScript strict mode
4. Follow Next.js 16 App Router conventions
5. Use Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed
